en there=E2=80=99s New York Sun publisher Dovid Efune, who now has backing =
from former Telegraph proprietor Conrad Black. On a related note, Rupert Mu=
rdoch is said to be interested in acquiring something, but I=E2=80=99m reli=
ably told it won=E2=80=99t be The Telegraph.
