ng interviews with tech luminaries=E2=80=94Steve Jobs, the sweating Mark Zu=
ckerberg, etcetera=E2=80=94Kara took on an =C3=A9minence grise role last ye=
ar and passed the reins to Nilay Patel, Casey Newton, and Julia Boorstin. A=
lready, Vox seems to have concluded that the new iteration isn=E2=80=99t wo=
rth the investment. Code, after all, was Kara=E2=80=99s thing. Now, confere=
nces have become the Zyns of the media business=E2=80=94addictive, sure, bu=
t high cost, low margin, and event production by another name. It was wise =
of C.E.O. Jim Bankoff to sunset this thing, even if many of us will miss th=
e after-hours poker game that Brooke Hammerling operated inside the Beverly=
 Hilton every year.

