           <p style=3D"margin: 0; color: #000000; font-size: 16px; line-hei=
ght: 30px; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 0;">Greetings from a comfortabl=
e cruising altitude, where I=E2=80=99m still recovering from Puck=E2=80=99s=
 <i>delightful</i> third-anniversary party, a capstone to our multiday <i>o=
n-</i>site off-site in New York. It was wonderful to see so many of you on =
the rooftop at Nine Orchard last night and to take stock of just how far we=
=E2=80=99ve come since our early days at 64 Bank Street. <br/><br/>Also, a =
very sincere thank-you for all the leads and tips you shared, which have gi=
ven me <i>a lot</i> to chase down in the days ahead. And thanks to whoever =
picked up the tab at the afterparty (wasn=E2=80=99t me). Anyway, it=E2=80=
=99s been a helluva week. I=E2=80=99m en route back to Los Angeles. If you=
=E2=80=99re headed west for the Emmys, I look forward to seeing you at bagg=
age claim.<br/><br/>In tonight=E2=80=99s email, news and notes on <b>Zaz</b=
>=E2=80=99s Charter deal, and what it does and <i>doesn=E2=80=99t</i> porte=
nd
for future negotiations with <b>Brian Roberts</b>. Plus, more on the Max-Pa=
ramount+ bundle.<br/><br/><i>But first=E2=80=A6</i><br/><br/></p><ul style=
=3D"margin:0;color:#000000;font-size:16px;line-height:30px;margin-top:0;mar=
gin-bottom:0;list-style-type:square;mso-special-format:bullet"><li><i>Zucke=
r=E2=80=99s game</i>: <b>Jeff Zucker</b>=E2=80=99s RedBird IMI recently suc=
ceeded in offloading <i>The Spectator</i> to hedge fund chief <b>Paul Marsh=
all </b>for an eye-popping =C2=A3100 million, and will accept final bids fo=
r <i>The Telegraph</i> in just two weeks. As you=E2=80=99ll recall, due to =
foreign ownership restrictions, the U.K. government forced Zucker to sell b=
oth the magazine and the paper shortly after he=E2=80=99d acquired them.<br=
/><br/>It=E2=80=99s unclear what <i>The Telegraph</i> will fetch: I=E2=80=
=99m told that subscription and revenue growth has slowed at the Tory broad=
sheet since Zucker first bought the asset. Meanwhile, the auction has been =
going on so long that the initial euphoria may have faded. Oh/and:
The anti-Zucker legislation that capped foreign sovereign ownership at 5 pe=
rcent has limited the available pool of prospective buyers.<br/><br/>So, wh=
o=E2=80=99s still in the mix? Three potential buyers: Marshall and <b>Ken G=
riffin </b>certainly have the money, and might like to pair <i>The</i> <i>T=
elegraph</i> with <i>The</i> <i>Spectator</i>. Former <i>Mirror </i>C.E.O. =
<b>David Montgomery </b>is also said to be in the swirl, though staff fear =
that he would be a ruthless cost-cutter (he is apparently referred to as =
=E2=80=9Cthe dour Ulsterman=E2=80=9D). And then there=E2=80=99s <i>New York=
 Sun </i>publisher <b>Dovid Efune</b>, who now has backing from former <i>T=
elegraph </i>proprietor <b>Conrad Black</b>. On a related note, <b>Rupert M=
urdoch</b> is said to be interested in acquiring <i>something</i>, but I=E2=
=80=99m reliably told it <i>won=E2=80=99t</i> be <i>The Telegraph.</i></li>=
<br/><li><i>End of Code</i>: Vox Media is suspending its Code Conference, t=
he annual two-day tech summit created by <b>Kara
Swisher </b>and <b>Walt Mossberg</b>. After more than 20 years of memorable=
, news-making interviews with tech luminaries=E2=80=94<b>Steve Jobs</b>, th=
e sweating <b>Mark Zuckerberg</b>, etcetera=E2=80=94Kara took on an <i>=C3=
=A9minence grise</i> role last year and passed the reins to <b>Nilay Patel<=
/b>,<b> Casey Newton</b>, and <b>Julia Boorstin</b>. Already, Vox seems to =
have concluded that the new iteration isn=E2=80=99t worth the investment. C=
ode, after all, was Kara=E2=80=99s thing. Now, conferences have become the =
Zyns of the media business=E2=80=94addictive, sure, but high cost, low marg=
in, and event production by another name. It was wise of C.E.O. <b>Jim Bank=
off </b>to sunset this <i>thing</i>, even if many of us will miss the after=
-hours poker game that <b>Brooke Hammerling </b>operated inside the Beverly=
 Hilton every year.</li></ul>
